agentVendorName.name: agentVendorName
agentVendorName.description: Displays the SNMP agent's manufacturer name.

agentProductName.name: agentProductName
agentProductName.description: Displays the product name that contains the SNMP agent.

agentChassisIndex.name: agentChassisIndex
agentChassisIndex.description: Displays which chassis contains the SNMP agent's module.

agentModuleIndex.name: agentModuleIndex
agentModuleIndex.description: Displays which module in the chassis is the SNMP agent's module. The chassis number is in the object agentChassisIndex.

mibversion.name: mibversion
mibversion.description: Displays the version of the MIB supported by the SNMP agent.

resetAgent.name: resetAgent
resetAgent.description: Performs a cold reset of the SNMP agent. If a new IP configuration was set, it will be used after the reset.

ipAddressMethodInUse.name: ipAddressMethodInUse
ipAddressMethodInUse.description: Displays how the IP address in use was determined. For example, fixed means the IP address was assigned by the user and stored within the Management Module. BOOTP means the SNMP agent used a BOOTP server to get its IP configuration.

ipAddressInUse.name: ipAddressInUse
ipAddressInUse.description: Displays the IP address currently in use.

gatewayorRouterAddrInUse.name: gatewayorRouterAddrInUse
gatewayorRouterAddrInUse.description: Displays the default gateway address currently in use. This is the device that routes to a different network. Usually a router or a routing server.

networkMaskInUse.name: networkMaskInUse
networkMaskInUse.description: Displays the network (subnet) mask currently in use. This must match the masks of other devices on the same network.

broadcastAddressInUse.name: broadcastAddressInUse
broadcastAddressInUse.description: Displays the broadcast address currently in use.

ipAddressMethodNextReset.name: ipAddressMethodNextReset
ipAddressMethodNextReset.description: Displays how the IP address will be determined after the SNMP agent is reset. For example, fixed means the IP address will be determined locally. BOOTP means the SNMP agent will search for a BOOTP server to get its IP configuration.

ipAddressNextReset.name: ipAddressNextReset
ipAddressNextReset.description: Displays the IP address the SNMP agent will use the next time it is reset.

gatewayorRouterAddrNextReset.name: gatewayorRouterAddrNextReset
gatewayorRouterAddrNextReset.description: Displays the default gateway the SNMP agent will use the next time it is reset.

networkMaskNextReset.name: networkMaskNextReset
networkMaskNextReset.description: Displays the netmask (subnet mask) the SNMP agent will use the next time it is reset.

snmpReadCommunityString.name: snmpReadCommunityString
snmpReadCommunityString.description: Sets the password for reads from the SNMP agent's MIB.

snmpWriteCommunityString.name: snmpWriteCommunityString
snmpWriteCommunityString.description: Sets the password for writes to the SNMP agent's MIB.

snmpTrapReceiverMAX.name: snmpTrapReceiverMAX
snmpTrapReceiverMAX.description: Displays the maximum number of trap receiving stations.

snmpTrapReceiverNumber.name: snmpTrapReceiverNumber
snmpTrapReceiverNumber.description: Displays the current number of trap receiving stations.

snmpTrapAddressTable.name: snmpTrapAddressTable
snmpTrapAddressTable.description: Contains information on individual trap receiving stations.

trapAddrIndex.name: trapAddrIndex
trapAddrIndex.description: Displays the index number of the trap receiving station.

trapIPAddr.name: trapIPAddr
trapIPAddr.description: Sets the IP address for a trap receiving station.

trapCommunityString.name: trapCommunityString
trapCommunityString.description: Sets the password for sending traps from the SNMP agent to the SNMP application on the trap receiving station.

trapStatus.name: trapStatus
trapStatus.description: Displays whether traps should be sent to this station (active) or whether traps should not be sent to this station (ignore).
